result.name: 1991-1991-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-1991-eastern-irish-sea-gro
result.notes:
A series of groundfish surveys were carried out from 1976 to 1991 in the 
eastern Irish Sea. Fishing took place using a Boris Goshawk trawl towed for an 
hour. This data is from the 1 survey carried out in 1991. Numbers at length by 
centimetre of the main commercial fish species are recorded. Station positions 
by area are recorded. A summary table is included containing catch data for 
all other species.
